## Best Practices

### Epic Writing
- Focus on business outcomes, not technical implementation
- Use active voice and present tense
- Be specific about persona (GCC recruiter, not just "user")
- Keep it concise (2-3 sentences)
- Include measurable business value in the "So that" clause

### Epic draft files
- Include a one-line **Epic summary** for the future Jira Summary field
- **Jira-ready description** section should mirror what 430 will paste into Jira
- Link to PRD path in the draft front matter

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid

- ❌ Writing epics as technical tasks ("Build scheduling API")
- ❌ Vague personas ("user", "someone")
- ❌ Missing business outcome (no "So that" clause)
- ❌ Implementation details in epic story ("using React and GraphQL")
- ❌ Creating epics without reading PRD context
- ❌ **Calling Jira MCP from 410** (forbidden — use 430 after 420 approval)

